  9     KEY_TAB : 9,
 10     KEY_RETURN : 13,

 28 hui.browser.opera = /opera/i.test(navigator.userAgent);
 29 hui.browser.msie = !hui.browser.opera && /MSIE/.test(navigator.userAgent);
 30 hui.browser.msie6 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 6')!==-1;
 31 hui.browser.msie7 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 7')!==-1;
 32 hui.browser.msie8 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 8')!==-1;
 33 hui.browser.msie9 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 9')!==-1;
 34 hui.browser.webkit = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('WebKit')!==-1;
 35 hui.browser.safari = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Safari')!==-1;
 36 hui.browser.webkitVersion = null;
 37 hui.browser.gecko = !hui.browser.webkit && navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Gecko')!=-1;
 38 
 39 hui.browser.opacity = !hui.browser.msie || hui.browser.msie9;
 40 
 41 (function() {
 42 	var result = /Safari\/([\d.]+)/.exec(navigator.userAgent);
 43 	if (result) {
 44 		hui.browser.webkitVersion=parseFloat(result[1]);
 45 	}
 46 })()

 48 /** Log something */
 49 hui.log = function(obj) {
 50 	try {
 51 		console.log(obj);
 52 	} catch (ignore) {};
 53 }
 54 
 55 /** Override the properties on the first argument with properties from the last object */
 56 hui.override = function(original,subject) {
 57 	if (subject) {
 58 		for (prop in subject) {
 59 			original[prop] = subject[prop];
 60 		}
 61 	}
 62 	return original;
 63 }
 64 
 65 /** Inserts invisible break chars in string so it will wrap */
 66 hui.wrap = function(str) {
 67 	if (str===null || str===undefined) {
 68 		return '';
 69 	}
 70 	return str.split('').join("\u200B");
 71 }
 72 
 73 /** Trim whitespace including unicode chars */
 74 hui.trim = function(str) {
 75 	if (str===null || str===undefined) {return ''};
 76 	if (typeof(str)!='string') {str=new String(str)}
 77 	return str.replace(/^[\s\x0b\xa0\u2000\u2001\u2002\u2003\u2004\u2005\u2006\u2007\u2008\u2009\u200a\u200b\u2028\u2029\u3000]+|[\s\x0b\xa0\u2000\u2001\u2002\u2003\u2004\u2005\u2006\u2007\u2008\u2009\u200a\u200b\u2028\u2029\u3000]+$/g, '');
 78 }
 79 
 80 /** Escape the html in a string */
 81 hui.escapeHTML = function(str) {
 82 	if (str===null || str===undefined) {return ''};
 83    	return hui.build('div',{text:str}).innerHTML;
 84 }
 85 
 86 hui.escape = function(str) {
 87 	if (!hui.isDefined(str)) {return ''};
 88 	return str.replace(/&/g,'&').
 89 		replace(/>/g,'>').
 90 		replace(/</g,'<').
 91 		replace(/"/g,'"')
 92 }
 93 
 94 /** Checks if a string has characters */
 95 hui.isBlank = function(str) {
 96 	if (str===null || typeof(str)==='undefined' || str==='') {return true};
 97 	return typeof(str)=='string' && hui.trim(str).length==0;
 98 }
 99 
100 hui.isEmpty = function(str) {
101 	hui.log('hui.isEmpty is deprecated');
102 	return hui.isBlank(str);
103 }
104 
105 /** Checks that an object is not null or undefined */
106 hui.isDefined = function(obj) {
107 	return obj!==null && typeof(obj)!=='undefined';
108 }
109 
110 hui.isArray = function(obj) {
111 	if (obj==null || obj==undefined) {
112 		return false;
113 	}
114 	if (obj.constructor == Array) {
115 		return true;
116 	} else {
117 		return Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === '[object Array]';
118 	}
119 }

121 /** @namespace */
122 hui.string = {
123 	
124 	/**
125 	Test that a string ends with another string
126 	@param str The string to test
127 	@param end The string to look for at the end
128 	*/
129 	endsWith : function(str,end) {
130 		if (!typeof(str)=='string' || !typeof(end)=='string') {
131 			return false;
132 		}
133 		return (str.match(end+"$")==end);
134 	},
135 	
136 	/** Make a string camelized */
137 	camelize : function(str) {
138 		if (str.indexOf('-')==-1) {return str}
139 	    var oStringList = str.split('-');
140 
141 	    var camelizedString = str.indexOf('-') == 0
142 	      ? oStringList[0].charAt(0).toUpperCase() + oStringList[0].substring(1)
143 	      : oStringList[0];
144 
145 	    for (var i = 1, len = oStringList.length; i < len; i++) {
146 	      var s = oStringList[i];
147 	      camelizedString += s.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + s.substring(1);
148 	    }
149 
150 	    return camelizedString;
151 	}
152 }
153 
154 hui.inArray = function(arr,value) {
155 	for (var i=0; i < arr.length; i++) {
156 		if (arr[i]===value) {
157 			return true;
158 		}
159 	};
160 	return false;
161 }
162 
163 hui.indexInArray = function(arr,value) {
164 	for (var i=0; i < arr.length; i++) {
165 		if (arr[i]===value) {
166 			return i;
167 		}
168 	};
169 	return -1;
170 }
171 
172 hui.each = function(items,func) {
173 	if (hui.isArray(items)) {		
174 		for (var i=0; i < items.length; i++) {
175 			func(items[i],i);
176 		};
177 	} else {
178 		for (var key in items) {
179 			func(key,items[key]);
180 		}
181 	}
182 }
183 
184 /**
185  * Converts a string to an int if it is only digits, otherwise remains a string
186  */
187 hui.intOrString = function(str) {
188 	if (hui.isDefined(str)) {
189 		var result = /[0-9]+/.exec(str);
190 		if (result!==null && result[0]==str) {
191 			if (parseInt(str,10)==str) {
192 				return parseInt(str,10);
193 			}
194 		}
195 	}
196 	return str;
197 }
198 
199 hui.flipInArray = function(arr,value) {
200 	if (hui.inArray(arr,value)) {
201 		hui.removeFromArray(arr,value);
202 	} else {
203 		arr.push(value);
204 	}
205 }
206 
207 hui.removeFromArray = function(arr,value) {
208 	for (var i = arr.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
209 		if (arr[i]==value) {
210 			arr.splice(i,1);
211 		}
212 	};
213 }
214 
215 hui.addToArray = function(arr,value) {
216 	if (value.constructor==Array) {
217 		for (var i=0; i < value.length; i++) {
218 			if (!hui.inArray(arr,value[i])) {
219 				arr.push(value);
220 			}
221 		};
222 	} else {
223 		if (!hui.inArray(arr,value)) {
224 			arr.push(value);
225 		}
226 	}
227 }
228 
229 hui.toIntArray = function(str) {
230 	var array = str.split(',');
231 	for (var i = array.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
232 		array[i] = parseInt(array[i]);
233 	};
234 	return array;
235 }
236 
237 hui.scrollTo = function(element) {
238 	element = hui.get(element);
239 	if (element) {
240 		var pos = hui.getPosition(element);
241 		window.scrollTo(pos.left, pos.top-50);
242 	}
243 }

247 /** @namespace */
248 hui.dom = {
249 	isElement : function(n,name) {
250 		return n.nodeType==hui.ELEMENT_NODE && (name===undefined ? true : n.nodeName.toLowerCase()==name);
251 	},
252 	isDefinedText : function(node) {
253 		return node.nodeType==hui.TEXT_NODE && node.nodeValue.length>0;
254 	},
255 	addText : function(node,text) {
256 		node.appendChild(document.createTextNode(text));
257 	},
258 	clear : function(node) {
259 		var children = node.childNodes;
260 		for (var i = children.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
261 			children[i].parentNode.removeChild(children[i]);
262 		};
263 	},
264 	remove : function(node) {
265 		if (node.parentNode) {
266 			node.parentNode.removeChild(node);
267 		}
268 	},
269 	replaceNode : function(oldNode,newNode) {
270 		newNode.parentNode.removeChild(newNode);
271 		oldNode.parentNode.insertBefore(newNode,oldNode);
272 		oldNode.parentNode.removeChild(oldNode);
273 	},
274 	replaceHTML : function(node,html) {
275 		node = hui.get(node);
276 		node.innerHTML=html;
277 	},
278 	runScripts : function(node) {
279 		var scripts = node.getElementsByTagName('script');
280 		for (var i=0; i < scripts.length; i++) {
281 			eval(scripts[i].innerHTML);
282 		}
283 	},
284 	setText : function(node,text) {
285 		var c = node.childNodes;
286 		var updated = false;
287 		for (var i = c.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
288 			if (!updated && c[i].nodeType==hui.TEXT_NODE) {
289 				c[i].nodeValue=text;
290 				updated = true;
291 			} else {
292 				node.removeChild(c[i]);
293 			}
294 		}
295 		if (!updated) {
296 			hui.dom.addText(node,text);
297 		}
298 	},
299 	getText : function(node) {
300 		var txt = '';
301 		var c = node.childNodes;
302 		for (var i=0; i < c.length; i++) {
303 			if (c[i].nodeType==hui.TEXT_NODE && c[i].nodeValue!=null) {
304 				txt+=c[i].nodeValue;
305 			} else if (c[i].nodeType==hui.ELEMENT_NODE) {
306 				txt+=hui.dom.getText(c[i]);
307 			}
308 		};
309 		return txt;
310 	},
311 	isVisible : function(node) {
312 		while (node) {
313 			if (node.style && (hui.getStyle(node,'display')==='none' || hui.getStyle(node,'visibility')==='hidden')) {
314 				return false;
315 			}
316 			node = node.parentNode;
317 		}
318 		return true;
319 	}
320 }
321 
322 hui.form = {
323 	getValues : function(node) {
324 		var params = {};
325 		var inputs = node.getElementsByTagName('input');
326 		for (var i=0; i < inputs.length; i++) {
327 			if (hui.isDefined(inputs[i].name)) {
328 				params[inputs[i].name] = inputs[i].value;
329 			}
330 		};
331 		return params;
332 	}
333 }

337 hui.get = function(str) {
338 	if (typeof(str)=='string') {
339 		return document.getElementById(str);
340 	}
341 	return str;
342 }
343 
344 hui.getChildren = function(node) {
345 	var children = [];
346 	var x = node.childNodes;
347 	for (var i=0; i < x.length; i++) {
348 		if (hui.dom.isElement(x[i])) {
349 			children.push(x[i]);
350 		}
351 	};
352 	return children;
353 }

356 if (document.querySelector) {
357 	hui.firstByClass = function(parentElement,className,tag) {
358 		parentElement = parentElement || document.body;
359 		return parentElement.querySelector((tag ? tag+'.' : '.')+className);
360 	}
361 } else {
362 	hui.firstByClass = function(parentElement,className,tag) {
363 		var children = (hui.get(parentElement) || document.body).getElementsByTagName(tag || '*');
364 		for (var i=0;i<children.length;i++) {
365 			if (hui.hasClass(children[i],className)) {
366 				return children[i];
367 			}
368 		}
369 		return null;
370 	}
371 }
372 
373 if (document.querySelectorAll) {
374 	hui.byClass = function(parentElement,className,tag) {
375 		parentElement = parentElement || document.body;
376 		var nl = parentElement.querySelectorAll((tag ? tag+'.' : '.')+className);
377 		// Important to convert into array...
378 		var l=[];
379 		for(var i=0, ll=nl.length; i!=ll; l.push(nl[i++]));
380 		return l;
381 	}
382 } else {
383 	hui.byClass = function(parentElement,className,tag) {
384 		var children = (hui.get(parentElement) || document.body).getElementsByTagName(tag || '*'),
385 			out = [];
386 		for (var i=0;i<children.length;i++) {
387 			if (hui.hasClass(children[i],className)) {
388 				out[out.length]=children[i];
389 			}
390 		}
391 		return out;
392 	}
393 }
394 
395 hui.byTag = function(node,name) {
396 	var nl = node.getElementsByTagName(name),
397 		l=[];
398 	for(var i=0, ll=nl.length; i!=ll; l.push(nl[i++]));
399 	return l;
400 }
401 
402 hui.byId = function(e,id) {
403 	var children = e.childNodes;
404 	for (var i = children.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
405 		if (children[i].nodeType===hui.ELEMENT_NODE && children[i].getAttribute('id')===id) {
406 			return children[i];
407 		} else {
408 			var found = hui.byId(children[i],id);
409 			if (found) {
410 				return found;
411 			}
412 		}
413 	}
414 	return null;
415 }
416 
417 hui.firstParentByTag = function(node,tag) {
418 	var parent = node;
419 	while (parent) {
420 		if (parent.tagName && parent.tagName.toLowerCase()==tag) {
421 			return parent;
422 		}
423 		parent = parent.parentNode;
424 	}
425 	return null;
426 }
427 
428 hui.firstParentByClass = function(node,tag) {
429 	var parent = node;
430 	while (parent) {
431 		if (hui.hasClass(parent)) {
432 			return parent;
433 		}
434 		parent = parent.parentNode;
435 	}
436 	return null;
437 }
438 
439 hui.firstByTag = function(parentElement,tag) {
440 	parentElement = hui.get(parentElement) || document.body;
441 	if (document.querySelector && tag!=='*') {
442 		return parentElement.querySelector(tag);
443 	}
444 	var children = parentElement.getElementsByTagName(tag);
445 	return children[0];
446 }
447 
448 hui.build = function(tag,options) {
449 	var e = document.createElement(tag);
450 	if (options) {
451 		for (prop in options) {
452 			if (prop=='text') {
453 				e.appendChild(document.createTextNode(options.text));
454 			} else if (prop=='html') {
455 				e.innerHTML=options.html;
456 			} else if (prop=='parent') {
457 				options.parent.appendChild(e);
458 			} else if (prop=='parentFirst') {
459 				if (options.parentFirst.childNodes.length==0) {
460 					options.parentFirst.appendChild(e);
461 				} else {
462 					options.parentFirst.insertBefore(e,options.parentFirst.childNodes[0]);
463 				}
464 			} else if (prop=='className') {
465 				e.className=options.className;
466 			} else if (prop=='class') {
467 				e.className=options['class'];
468 			} else if (prop=='style' && (hui.browser.msie7 || hui.browser.msie6)) {
469 				e.style.setAttribute('cssText',options[prop]);
470 			} else if (hui.isDefined(options[prop])) {
471 				e.setAttribute(prop,options[prop]);
472 			}
473 		}
474 	}
475 	return e;
476 }
477 
478 hui.getAncestors = function(element) {
479 	var ancestors = [];
480 	var parent = element.parentNode;
481 	while (parent) {
482 		ancestors[ancestors.length] = parent;
483 		parent = parent.parentNode;
484 	}
485 	return ancestors;
486 }
487 
488 hui.getNext = function(element) {
489 	if (!element) {
490 		return null;
491 	}
492 	if (!element.nextSibling) {
493 		return null;
494 	}
495 	var next = element.nextSibling;
496 	while (next && next.nodeType!=1) {
497 		next = next.nextSibling;
498 	}
499     return next;
500 }
501 
502 hui.getAllNext = function(element) {
503 	var elements = [];
504 	var next = hui.getNext(element);
505 	while (next) {
506 		elements.push(next);
507 		next = hui.getNext(next);
508 	}
509 	return elements;
510 }
511 
512 hui.getTop = function(element) {
513     element = hui.get(element);
514 	if (element) {
515 		var yPos = element.offsetTop;
516 		var tempEl = element.offsetParent;
517 		while (tempEl != null) {
518 			yPos += tempEl.offsetTop;
519 			tempEl = tempEl.offsetParent;
520 		}
521 		return yPos;
522 	}
523 	else return 0;
524 }
525 
526 hui.getLeft = function(element) {
527     element = hui.get(element);
528 	if (element) {
529 		var xPos = element.offsetLeft;
530 		var tempEl = element.offsetParent;
531 		while (tempEl != null) {
532 			xPos += tempEl.offsetLeft;
533 			tempEl = tempEl.offsetParent;
534 		}
535 		return xPos;
536 	}
537 	else return 0;
538 }
539 
540 hui.getPosition = function(element) {
541 	return {
542 		left : hui.getLeft(element),
543 		top : hui.getTop(element)
544 	}
545 }

547 /////////////////////////// Class handling //////////////////////
548 
549 hui.hasClass = function(element, className) {
550 	element = hui.get(element);
551 	if (!element || !element.className) {
552 		return false
553 	}
554 	var a = element.className.split(/\s+/);
555 	for (var i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
556 		if (a[i] == className) {
557 			return true;
558 		}
559 	}
560 	return false;
561 }
562 
563 hui.addClass = function(element, className) {
564     element = hui.get(element);
565 	if (!element) {return};
566 	
567     hui.removeClass(element, className);
568     element.className += ' ' + className;
569 }
570 
571 hui.removeClass = function(element, className) {
572 	element = hui.get(element);
573 	if (!element) {return};
574 
575 	var newClassName = '';
576 	var a = element.className.split(/\s+/);
577 	for (var i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
578 		if (a[i] != className) {
579 			if (i > 0) {
580 				newClassName += ' ';				
581 			}
582 			newClassName += a[i];
583 		}
584 	}
585 	element.className = newClassName;
586 }
587 
588 hui.toggleClass = function(element,className) {
589 	if (hui.hasClass(element,className)) {
590 		hui.removeClass(element,className);
591 	} else {
592 		hui.addClass(element,className);
593 	}
594 }
595 
596 hui.setClass = function(element,className,add) {
597 	if (add) {
598 		hui.addClass(element,className);
599 	} else {
600 		hui.removeClass(element,className);
601 	}
602 }

605 	return JSON.parse(json);
606 	//return eval('(' + json + ')');
607 }
608 
609 hui.toJSON = function(obj) {
610 	return JSON.stringify(obj);

615 hui.listen = function(el,type,listener,useCapture) {
616 	el = hui.get(el);
617 	if(document.addEventListener) {
618 		el.addEventListener(type,listener,useCapture ? true : false);
619 	} else {
620 		el.attachEvent('on'+type, listener);
621 	}
622 }
623 
624 hui.unListen = function(el,type,listener,useCapture) {
625 	el = hui.get(el);
626 	if(document.removeEventListener) {
627 		el.removeEventListener(type,listener,useCapture ? true : false);
628 	} else {
629 		el.detachEvent('on'+type, listener);
630 	}
631 }
632 
633 hui.event = function(event) {
634 	return new hui.Event(event);
635 }
636 
637 hui.Event = function(event) {
638 	this.event = event = event || window.event;
639 	this.element = event.target ? event.target : event.srcElement;
640 	this.shiftKey = event.shiftKey;
641 	this.returnKey = event.keyCode==13;
642 	this.escapeKey = event.keyCode==27;
643 	this.spaceKey = event.keyCode==32;
644 	this.upKey = event.keyCode==38;
645 	this.downKey = event.keyCode==40;
646 	this.leftKey = event.keyCode==37;
647 	this.rightKey = event.keyCode==39;
648 	this.keyCode = event.keyCode;
649 }
650 
651 hui.Event.prototype = {
652 	left : function() {
653 	    var left = 0;
654 		if (this.event) {
655 		    if (this.event.pageX) {
656 			    left = this.event.pageX;
657 		    } else if (this.event.clientX) {
658 			    left = this.event.clientX + hui.getScrollLeft();
659 		    }
660 		}
661 	    return left;
662 	},
663 	getLeft : function() {
664 		return this.left();
665 	},
666 	top : function() {
667 	    var top = 0;
668 		if (this.event) {
669 		    if (this.event.pageY) {
670 			    top = this.event.pageY;
671 		    } else if (this.event.clientY) {
672 			    top = this.event.clientY + hui.getScrollTop();
673 		    }
674 		}
675 	    return top;
676 	},
677 	getTop : function() {
678 		return this.top();
679 	},
680 	getElement : function() {
681 		return this.element;
682 	},
683 	findByClass : function(cls) {
684 		var parent = this.element;
685 		while (parent) {
686 			if (hui.hasClass(parent,cls)) {
687 				return parent;
688 			}
689 			parent = parent.parentNode;
690 		}
691 		return null;
692 	},
693 	findByTag : function(tag) {
694 		var parent = this.element;
695 		while (parent) {
696 			if (parent.tagName && parent.tagName.toLowerCase()==tag) {
697 				return parent;
698 			}
699 			parent = parent.parentNode;
700 		}
701 		return null;
702 	},
703 
704 	stop : function() {
705 		hui.stop(this.event);
706 	}
707 }
708 
709 hui.stop = function(e) {
710 	if (!e) {e = window.event};
711 	if (e.stopPropagation) {e.stopPropagation()};
712 	if (e.preventDefault) {e.preventDefault()};
713 	e.cancelBubble = true;
714     e.stopped = true;
715 }
716 
717 hui.onReady = function(delegate) {
718 	if(window.addEventListener) {
719 		window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded',delegate,false);
720 	}
721 	else if(typeof document.addEventListener != 'undefined')
722 	{
723 		//.. opera 7
724 		document.addEventListener('load', delegate, false);
725 	}
726 	else if(typeof window.attachEvent != 'undefined')
727 	{
728 		//.. win/ie
729 		window.attachEvent('onload', delegate);
730 	}
731 
732 	//** remove this condition to degrade older browsers
733 	else
734 	{
735 		//.. mac/ie5 and anything else that gets this far
736 	
737 		//if there's an existing onload function
738 		if(typeof window.onload == 'function')
739 		{
740 			//store it
741 			var existing = window.onload;
742 		
743 			//add new onload handler
744 			window.onload = function()
745 			{
746 				//call existing onload function
747 				existing();
748 			
749 				//call delegate onload function
750 				delegate();
751 			};
752 		}
753 		else
754 		{
755 			//setup onload function
756 			window.onload = delegate;
757 		}
758 	}
759 }

761 // Ajax //
762 
763 hui.request = function(options) {
764 	options = hui.override({method:'POST',async:true},options);
765 	var transport = hui.request.createTransport();
766 	transport.onreadystatechange = function() {
767 		try {
768 			if (transport.readyState == 4) {
769 				if (transport.status == 200 && options.onSuccess) {
770 					options.onSuccess(transport);
771 				} else if (options.onFailure) {
772 					options.onFailure(transport);
773 				}
774 			}
775 		} catch (e) {
776 			if (options.onException) {
777 				options.onException(e,transport)
778 			} else {
779 				throw e;
780 			}
781 		}
782 	};
783 	var method = options.method.toUpperCase();
784 	transport.open(method, options.url, options.async);
785 	var body = '';
786     if (method=='POST' && options.parameters) {
787 		body = hui.request.buildPostBody(options.parameters);
788 		transport.setRequestHeader("Content-type", "application/x-www-form-urlencoded; charset=utf-8");
789 	}
790 	transport.send(body);
791 }
792 
793 hui.request.isXMLResponse = function(t) {
794 	return t.responseXML && t.responseXML.documentElement && t.responseXML.documentElement.nodeName!='parsererror';
795 }
796 
797 hui.request.buildPostBody = function(parameters) {
798 	if (!parameters) return null;
799 	var output = '';
800 	for (param in parameters) {
801 		if (output.length>0) output+='&';
802 		output+=encodeURIComponent(param)+'=';
803 		if (parameters[param]!==undefined && parameters[param]!==null) {
804 			output+=encodeURIComponent(parameters[param]);
805 		}
806 	}
807 	return output;
808 }
809 
810 hui.request.createTransport = function() {
811 	try {
812 		if (window.XMLHttpRequest) {
813 			var req = new XMLHttpRequest();
814 			if (req.readyState == null) {
815 				req.readyState = 1;
816 				req.addEventListener("load", function () {
817 					req.readyState = 4;
818 					if (typeof req.onreadystatechange == "function")
819 						req.onreadystatechange();
820 				}, false);
821 			}
822 			return req;
823 		}
824 		else if (window.ActiveXObject) {
825 			return hui.request.getActiveX();
826 		} else {
827 			// Could not create transport
828 			this.delegate.onError(this);
829 		}
830 	}
831 	catch (ex) {
832 		if (this.delegate.onError) {
833 			this.delegate.onError(this,ex);
834 		}
835 	}
836 }
837 
838 hui.request.getActiveX = function() {
839 	var prefixes = ["MSXML2", "Microsoft", "MSXML", "MSXML3"];
840 	var o;
841 	for (var i = 0; i < prefixes.length; i++) {
842 		try {
843 			// try to create the objects
844 			o = new ActiveXObject(prefixes[i] + ".XmlHttp");
845 			return o;
846 		}
847 		catch (ex) {};
848 	}
849 	
850 	throw new Error("Could not find an installed XML parser");
851 }

853 ///////////////////// Style ///////////////////
854 
855 hui.getStyle = function(element, style) {
856 	element = hui.get(element);
857 	var cameled = hui.string.camelize(style);
858 	var value = element.style[cameled];
859 	if (!value) {
860 		if (document.defaultView && document.defaultView.getComputedStyle) {
861 			var css = document.defaultView.getComputedStyle(element, null);
862 			value = css ? css.getPropertyValue(style) : null;
863 		} else if (element.currentStyle) {
864 			value = element.currentStyle[cameled];
865 		}
866 	}
867 	if (window.opera && ['left', 'top', 'right', 'bottom'].include(style)) {
868 		if (hui.getStyle(element, 'position') == 'static') value = 'auto';
869 	}
870 	return value == 'auto' ? null : value;
871 }
872 
873 hui.getTopPad = function(element) {
874 	var all,top;
875 	all = parseInt(hui.getStyle(element,'padding'),10);
876 	top = parseInt(hui.getStyle(element,'padding-top'),10);
877 	if (all) {return all;}
878 	if (top) {return top;}
879 	return 0;
880 }
881 
882 hui.getBottomPad = function(element) {
883 	var all,bottom;
884 	all = parseInt(hui.getStyle(element,'padding'),10);
885 	bottom = parseInt(hui.getStyle(element,'padding-bottom'),10);
886 	if (all) {return all;}
887 	if (bottom) {return bottom;}
888 	return 0;
889 }

891 hui.setOpacity = function(element,opacity) {
892 	if (!hui.browser.opacity) {
893 		if (opacity==1) {
894 			element.style['filter']=null;
895 		} else {
896 			element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
897 		}
898 	} else {
899 		element.style['opacity']=opacity;
900 	}
901 }
902 
903 hui.setStyle = function(element,styles) {
904 	for (style in styles) {
905 		if (style==='opacity') {
906 			hui.setOpacity(element,styles[style]);
907 		} else {
908 			element.style[style] = styles[style];
909 		}
910 	}
911 }
912 
913 hui.copyStyle = function(source,target,styles) {
914 	for (var i=0; i < styles.length; i++) {
915 		var s = styles[i];
916 		var r = hui.getStyle(source,s);
917 		if (r) {
918 			target.style[s] = r;
919 		}
920 	};
921 }

945 hui.getSelectedText = function(doc) {
946 	doc = doc || document;
947 	if (doc.getSelection) {
948 		return doc.getSelection()+'';
949 	} else if (doc.selection) {
950 		return doc.selection.createRange().text;
951 	}
952 	return '';
953 }
954 
955 hui.selection = {
956 	clear : function() { 
957 		var sel ; 
958 		if(document.selection && document.selection.empty	){ 
959 			document.selection.empty() ; 
960 		} else if(window.getSelection) { 
961 			sel=window.getSelection();
962 			if(sel && sel.removeAllRanges) {
963 				sel.removeAllRanges() ; 
964 			}
965 		}
966 	},
967 	getText : function(doc) {
968 		doc = doc || document;
969 		if (doc.getSelection) {
970 			return doc.getSelection()+'';
971 		} else if (doc.selection) {
972 			return doc.selection.createRange().text;
973 		}
974 		return '';
975 	}

980 hui.effect = {
981 	makeFlippable : function(options) {
982 		if (hui.browser.webkit) {
983 			hui.addClass(options.container,'hui_flip_container');
984 			hui.addClass(options.front,'hui_flip_front');
985 			hui.addClass(options.back,'hui_flip_back');
986 		} else {
987 			hui.addClass(options.front,'hui_flip_front_legacy');
988 			hui.addClass(options.back,'hui_flip_back_legacy');
989 		}
990 	},
991 	flip : function(options) {
992 		if (!hui.browser.webkit) {
993 			hui.toggleClass(options.element,'hui_flip_flipped_legacy');
994 		} else {
995 			var element = hui.get(options.element);
996 			var duration = options.duration || '1s';
997 			var front = hui.firstByClass(element,'hui_flip_front');
998 			var back = hui.firstByClass(element,'hui_flip_back');
999 			front.style.webkitTransitionDuration=duration;
1000 			back.style.webkitTransitionDuration=duration;
1001 			hui.toggleClass(options.element,'hui_flip_flipped');
1002 		}
1003 	}

1008 hui.getScrollTop = function() {
1009 	if (self.pageYOffset) {
1010 		return self.pageYOffset;
1011 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.scrollTop) {
1012 		return document.documentElement.scrollTop;
1013 	} else if (document.body) {
1014 		return document.body.scrollTop;
1015 	}
1016 }
1017 
1018 hui.getScrollLeft = function() {
1019 	if (self.pageYOffset) {
1020 		return self.pageXOffset;
1021 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.scrollTop) {
1022 		return document.documentElement.scrollLeft;
1023 	} else if (document.body) {
1024 		return document.body.scrollLeft;
1025 	}
1026 }

1028 /**
1029  * Get the height of the viewport
1030  */
1031 hui.getViewPortHeight = function() {
1032 	if (window.innerHeight) {
1033 		return window.innerHeight;
1034 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.clientHeight) {
1035 		return document.documentElement.clientHeight;
1036 	} else if (document.body) {
1037 		return document.body.clientHeight;
1038 	}
1039 }
1040 
1041 /**
1042  * Get the height of the viewport
1043  */
1044 hui.getViewPortWidth = function() {
1045 	if (window.innerWidth) {
1046 		return window.innerWidth;
1047 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.clientWidth) {
1048 		return document.documentElement.clientWidth;
1049 	} else if (document.body) {
1050 		return document.body.clientWidth;
1051 	}
1052 }
1053 
1054 hui.getDocumentWidth = function() {
1055 	return Math.max(document.body.clientWidth,document.documentElement.clientWidth,document.documentElement.scrollWidth)
1056 	return document.body.scrollWidth;
1057 }
1058 
1059 hui.getDocumentHeight = function() {
1060 	if (hui.browser.msie6) {
1061 		// In IE6 check the children too
1062 		var max = Math.max(document.body.clientHeight,document.documentElement.clientHeight,document.documentElement.scrollHeight);
1063 		var children = document.body.childNodes;
1064 		for (var i=0; i < children.length; i++) {
1065 			if (hui.dom.isElement(children[i])) {
1066 				max = Math.max(max,children[i].clientHeight);
1067 			}
1068 		}
1069 		return max;
1070 	}
1071 	if (window.scrollMaxY && window.innerHeight) {
1072 		return window.scrollMaxY+window.innerHeight;
1073 	} else {
1074 		return Math.max(document.body.clientHeight,document.documentElement.clientHeight,document.documentElement.scrollHeight);
1075 	}
1076 }

1078 //////////////////////////// Placement /////////////////////////
1079 
1080 /**
1081  * Example hui.place({target : {element : myTarget, horizontal : 1}, source : {element : mySource, vertical : 0.5}})
1082  */
1083 hui.place = function(options) {
1084 	var left=0,top=0;
1085 	var trgt = options.target.element;
1086 	var trgtPos = {left:hui.getLeft(trgt),top:hui.getTop(trgt)};
1087 	left = trgtPos.left+trgt.clientWidth*options.target.horizontal;
1088 	top = trgtPos.top+trgt.clientHeight*options.target.vertical;
1089 	
1090 	var src = options.source.element;
1091 	left-=src.clientWidth*options.source.horizontal;
1092 	top-=src.clientHeight*options.source.vertical;
1093 	
1094 	if (options.insideViewPort) {
1095 		var w = hui.getViewPortWidth();
1096 		hui.log((left+src.clientWidth)+'>'+w);
1097 		if (left+src.clientWidth>w) {
1098 			left=w-src.clientWidth;
1099 		}
1100 		if (left<0) {left=0}
1101 		if (top<0) {top=0}
1102 	}
1103 	
1104 	src.style.top=top+'px';
1105 	src.style.left=left+'px';
1106 }

1110 /** @constructor
1111  * @param options {context:prefix for urls}
1112  */
1113 hui.Preloader = function(options) {
1114 	this.options = options || {};
1115 	this.delegate = {};
1116 	this.images = [];
1117 	this.loaded = 0;
1118 }
1119 
1120 hui.Preloader.prototype = {
1121 	/** Add images either as a single url or an array of urls */
1122 	addImages : function(imageOrImages) {
1123 		if (typeof(imageOrImages)=='object') {
1124 			for (var i=0; i < imageOrImages.length; i++) {
1125 				this.images.push(imageOrImages[i]);
1126 			};
1127 		} else {
1128 			this.images.push(imageOrImages);
1129 		}
1130 	},
1131 	/** Set the delegate (listener) */
1132 	setDelegate : function(d) {
1133 		this.delegate = d;
1134 	},
1135 	/**
1136 	 * Start loading images beginning at startIndex
1137 	 */
1138 	load : function(startIndex) {
1139 		startIndex = startIndex || 0;
1140 		var self = this;
1141 		this.obs = [];
1142 		for (var i=startIndex; i < this.images.length+startIndex; i++) {
1143 			var index=i;
1144 			if (index>=this.images.length) {
1145 				index = index-this.images.length;
1146 			}
1147 			var img = new Image();
1148 			img.huiPreloaderIndex = index;
1149 			img.onload = function() {self._imageChanged(this.huiPreloaderIndex,'imageDidLoad')};
1150 			img.onerror = function() {self._imageChanged(this.huiPreloaderIndex,'imageDidGiveError')};
1151 			img.onabort = function() {self._imageChanged(this.huiPreloaderIndex,'imageDidAbort')};
1152 			img.src = (this.options.context ? this.options.context : '')+this.images[index];
1153 			this.obs.push(img);
1154 		};
1155 	},
1156 	_imageChanged : function(index,method) {
1157 		this.loaded++;
1158 		if (this.delegate[method]) {
1159 			this.delegate[method](this.loaded,this.images.length,index);
1160 		}
1161 		if (this.loaded==this.images.length && this.delegate.allImagesDidLoad) {
1162 			this.delegate.allImagesDidLoad();
1163 		}
1164 	}
1165 }

1167 /** @namespace */
1168 hui.cookie = {
1169 	/** Adds a cookie value by name */
1170 	set : function(name,value,days) {
1171 		var expires;
1172 		if (days) {
1173 			var date = new Date();
1174 			date.setTime(date.getTime()+(days*24*60*60*1000));
1175 			expires = "; expires="+date.toGMTString();
1176 		} else {
1177 			expires = "";
1178 		}
1179 		document.cookie = name+"="+value+expires+"; path=/";
1180 	},
1181 	/** Gets a cookie value by name */
1182 	get : function(name) {
1183 		var nameEQ = name + "=";
1184 		var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
1185 		for(var i=0;i < ca.length;i++) {
1186 			var c = ca[i];
1187 			while (c.charAt(0)==' ') {
1188 				c = c.substring(1,c.length);
1189 			}
1190 			if (c.indexOf(nameEQ) == 0) {
1191 				return c.substring(nameEQ.length,c.length);
1192 			}
1193 		}
1194 		return null;
1195 	},
1196 	/** Clears a cookie by name */
1197 	clear : function(name) {
1198 		this.set(name,"",-1);
1199 	}
1200 }

1204 /** @constructor */
1205 hui.URL = function(url) {
1206 	this.url = url || '';
1207 }
1208 
1209 hui.URL.prototype = {
1210 	addParameter : function(key,value) {
1211 		this.url+=this.url.indexOf('?')!=-1 ? '&' : '?';
1212 		this.url+=key+'='+(hui.isDefined(value) ? value : '');
1213 	},
1214 	toString : function() {
1215 		return this.url;
1216 	}
1217 }

1219 /** @namespace */
1220 hui.location = {
1221 	/** Get an URL parameter */
1222 	getParameter : function(name) {
1223 		var parms = hui.location.getParameters();
1224 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
1225 			if (parms[i].name==name) {
1226 				return parms[i].value;
1227 			}
1228 		};
1229 		return null;
1230 	},
1231 	/** Set an URL parameter - initiates a new request */
1232 	setParameter : function(name,value) {
1233 		var parms = hui.location.getParameters();
1234 		var found = false;
1235 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
1236 			if (parms[i].name==name) {
1237 				parms[i].value=value;
1238 				found=true;
1239 				break;
1240 			}
1241 		};
1242 		if (!found) {
1243 			parms.push({name:name,value:value});
1244 		}
1245 		hui.location.setParameters(parms);
1246 	},
1247 	/** Checks if the URL has a certain hash */
1248 	hasHash : function(name) {
1249 		var h = document.location.hash;
1250 		if (h!=='') {
1251 			return h=='#'+name;
1252 		}
1253 		return false;
1254 	},
1255 	/** Gets a hash parameter (#name=value&other=text) */
1256 	getHashParameter : function(name) {
1257 		var h = document.location.hash;
1258 		if (h!=='') {
1259 			var i = h.indexOf(name+'=');
1260 			if (i!==-1) {
1261 				var remaining = h.substring(i+name.length+1);
1262 				if (remaining.indexOf('&')!==-1) {
1263 					return remaining.substring(0,remaining.indexOf('&'));
1264 				}
1265 				return remaining;
1266 			}
1267 		}
1268 		return null;
1269 	},
1270 	/** Clears the URL hash */
1271 	clearHash : function() {
1272 		document.location.hash='#';
1273 	},
1274 	/** Sets a number of parameters
1275 	 * @param params Array of parameters [{name:'hep',value:'hey'}]
1276 	 */
1277 	setParameters : function(parms) {
1278 		var query = '';
1279 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
1280 			query+= i==0 ? '?' : '&';
1281 			query+=parms[i].name+'='+parms[i].value;
1282 		};
1283 		document.location.search=query;
1284 	},
1285 	/** Checks if a parameter exists with the value 'true' or 1 */
1286 	getBoolean : function(name) {
1287 		var value = hui.location.getParameter(name);
1288 		return (value=='true' || value=='1');
1289 	},
1290 	/** Gets all parameters as an array like : [{name:'hep',value:'hey'}] */
1291 	getParameters : function() {
1292 		var items = document.location.search.substring(1).split('&');
1293 		var parsed = [];
1294 		for( var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
1295 			var item = items[i].split('=');
1296 			var name = unescape(item[0]).replace(/^\s*|\s*$/g,"");
1297 			var value = unescape(item[1]).replace(/^\s*|\s*$/g,"");
1298 			if (name) {
1299 				parsed.push({name:name,value:value});
1300 			}
1301 		};
1302 		return parsed;
1303 	}	
1304 };

1308 
1309 hui.ani = hui.animate = function(element,style,value,duration,delegate) {
1310 	hui.animation.get(element).animate(null,value,style,duration,delegate);
1311 }
1312 
1313 /** @namespace */
1314 hui.animation = {
1315 	objects : {},
1316 	running : false,
1317 	latestId : 0,
1318 	get : function(element) {
1319 		element = hui.get(element);
1320 		if (!element.n2iAnimationId) {
1321 			element.n2iAnimationId = this.latestId++;
1322 		}
1323 		if (!this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId]) {
1324 			this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId] = new hui.animation.Item(element);
1325 		}
1326 		return this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId];
1327 	},
1328 	start : function() {
1329 		if (!this.running) {
1330 			hui.animation.render();
1331 		}
1332 	}
1333 };
1334 
1335 hui.animation.render = function(element) {
1336 	this.running = true;
1337 	var next = false;
1338 	var stamp = new Date().getTime();
1339 	for (var id in this.objects) {
1340 		var obj = this.objects[id];
1341 		if (obj.work) {
1342 			for (var i=0; i < obj.work.length; i++) {
1343 				var work = obj.work[i];
1344 				if (work.finished) continue;
1345 				var place = (stamp-work.start)/(work.end-work.start);
1346 				if (place<0) {
1347 					next=true;
1348 					continue;
1349 				}
1350 				else if (isNaN(place)) place = 1;
1351 				else if (place>1) place=1;
1352 				else if (place<1) next=true;
1353 				var v = place;
1354 				if (work.delegate && work.delegate.ease) {
1355 					v = work.delegate.ease(v);
1356 				}
1357 				var value = null;
1358 				if (work.delegate && work.delegate.callback) {
1359 					work.delegate.callback(obj.element,v);
1360 				} else if (!work.css) {
1361 					obj.element[work.property] = Math.round(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
1362 				} else if (work.property=='transform' && !hui.browser.msie) {
1363 					var t = work.transform;
1364 					var str = '';
1365 					if (t.rotate) {
1366 						str+=' rotate('+(t.rotate.from+(t.rotate.to-t.rotate.from)*v)+t.rotate.unit+')';
1367 					}
1368 					if (t.scale) {
1369 						str+=' scale('+(t.scale.from+(t.scale.to-t.scale.from)*v)+')';
1370 					}
1371 					obj.element.style[hui.animation.TRANSFORM]=str;
1372 				} else if (work.to.red!=null) {
1373 					var red = Math.round(work.from.red+(work.to.red-work.from.red)*v);
1374 					var green = Math.round(work.from.green+(work.to.green-work.from.green)*v);
1375 					var blue = Math.round(work.from.blue+(work.to.blue-work.from.blue)*v);
1376 					value = 'rgb('+red+','+green+','+blue+')';
1377 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
1378 				} else if (!hui.browser.opacity && work.property=='opacity') {
1379 					var opacity = (work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
1380 					if (opacity==1) {
1381 						obj.element.style.removeAttribute('filter');
1382 					} else {
1383 						obj.element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
1384 					}
1385 				} else {
1386 					value = new String(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v)+(work.unit!=null ? work.unit : '');
1387 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
1388 				}
1389 				if (place==1) {
1390 					work.finished = true;
1391 					if (work.delegate && work.delegate.onComplete) {
1392 						window.setTimeout(work.delegate.onComplete);
1393 					} else if (work.delegate && work.delegate.hideOnComplete) {
1394 						obj.element.style.display='none';
1395 					}
1396 				}
1397 			};
1398 		}
1399 	}
1400 	if (next) {
1401 		window.setTimeout(function() {
1402 			hui.animation.render();
1403 		},0);
1404 	} else {
1405 		this.running = false;
1406 	}
1407 }
1408 
1409 hui.animation.parseStyle = function(value) {
1410 	var parsed = {type:null,value:null,unit:null};
1411 	var match;
1412 	if (!hui.isDefined(value)) {
1413 		return parsed;
1414 	} else if (!isNaN(value)) {
1415 		parsed.value=parseFloat(value);
1416 	} else if (match=value.match(/([\-]?[0-9\.]+)(px|pt|%)/)) {
1417 		parsed.type = 'length';
1418 		parsed.value = parseFloat(match[1]);
1419 		parsed.unit = match[2];
1420 	} else if (match=value.match(/rgb\(([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+)\)/)) {
1421 		parsed.type = 'color';
1422 		parsed.value = {
1423 			red:parseInt(match[1]),
1424 			green:parseInt(match[2]),
1425 			blue:parseInt(match[3])
1426 		};
1427 	} else {
1428 		var color = new hui.Color(value);
1429 		if (color.ok) {
1430 			parsed.value = {
1431 				red:color.r,
1432 				green:color.g,
1433 				blue:color.b
1434 			};
1435 		}
1436 	}
1437 	return parsed;
1438 }
1439 
1440 ///////////////////////////// Item ///////////////////////////////
1441 
1442 hui.animation.Item = function(element) {
1443 	this.element = element;
1444 	this.work = [];
1445 }
1446 
1447 hui.animation.Item.prototype.animate = function(from,to,property,duration,delegate) {
1448 	var css = true;
1449 	if (property=='scrollLeft' || property=='scrollTop') {
1450 		css = false;
1451 	}
1452 	
1453 	var work = this.getWork(css ? hui.string.camelize(property) : property);
1454 	work.delegate = delegate;
1455 	work.finished = false;
1456 	work.css = css;
1457 	if (from!=null) {
1458 		work.from = from;
1459 	} else if (property=='transform') {
1460 		work.transform = hui.animation.Item.parseTransform(to,this.element);
1461 	} else if (work.css && !hui.browser.opacity && property=='opacity') {
1462 		work.from = this.getIEOpacity(this.element);
1463 	} else if (work.css) {
1464 		var style = hui.getStyle(this.element,property);
1465 		var parsedStyle = hui.animation.parseStyle(style);
1466 		work.from = parsedStyle.value;
1467 	} else {
1468 		work.from = this.element[property];
1469 	}
1470 	if (work.css) {
1471 		var parsed = hui.animation.parseStyle(to);
1472 		work.to = parsed.value;
1473 		work.unit = parsed.unit;
1474 	} else {
1475 		work.to = to;
1476 		work.unit = null;
1477 	}
1478 	work.start = new Date().getTime();
1479 	if (delegate && delegate.delay) {
1480 		work.start+=delegate.delay;
1481 	}
1482 	work.end = work.start+duration;
1483 	hui.animation.start();
1484 }
1485 
1486 hui.animation.TRANSFORM = hui.browser.gecko ? 'MozTransform' : 'WebkitTransform';
1487 
1488 hui.animation.Item.parseTransform = function(value,element) {
1489 	var result = {};
1490 	var from,fromMatch;
1491 	var rotateReg = /rotate\(([0-9\.]+)([a-z]+)\)/i;
1492 	var rotate = value.match(rotateReg);
1493 	if (rotate) {
1494 		from = 0;
1495 		if (element.style[hui.animation.TRANSFORM]) {
1496 			fromMatch = element.style[hui.animation.TRANSFORM].match(rotateReg);
1497 			if (fromMatch) {
1498 				from = parseFloat(fromMatch[1]);
1499 			}
1500 		}
1501 		result.rotate = {from:from,to:parseFloat(rotate[1]),unit:rotate[2]};
1502 	}
1503 	var scaleReg = /scale\(([0-9\.]+)\)/i;
1504 	var scale = value.match(scaleReg);
1505 	if (scale) {
1506 		from = 1;
1507 		if (element.style[hui.animation.TRANSFORM]) {
1508 			fromMatch = element.style[hui.animation.TRANSFORM].match(scaleReg);
1509 			if (fromMatch) {
1510 				from = parseFloat(fromMatch[1]);
1511 			}
1512 		}
1513 		result.scale = {from:from,to:parseFloat(scale[1])};
1514 	}
1515 	
1516 	return result;
1517 }
1518 
1519 hui.animation.Item.prototype.getIEOpacity = function(element) {
1520 	var filter = hui.getStyle(element,'filter').toLowerCase();
1521 	var match;
1522 	if (match = filter.match(/opacity=([0-9]+)/)) {
1523 		return parseFloat(match[1])/100;
1524 	} else {
1525 		return 1;
1526 	}
1527 }
1528 
1529 hui.animation.Item.prototype.getWork = function(property) {
1530 	for (var i=0; i < this.work.length; i++) {
1531 		if (this.work[i].property==property) {
1532 			return this.work[i];
1533 		}
1534 	};
1535 	var work = {property:property};
1536 	this.work[this.work.length] = work;
1537 	return work;
1538 }
1539 
1540 /////////////////////////////// Loop ///////////////////////////////////
1541 
1542 hui.animation.Loop = function(recipe) {
1543 	this.recipe = recipe;
1544 	this.position = -1;
1545 	this.running = false;
1546 }
1547 
1548 hui.animation.Loop.prototype.next = function() {
1549 	this.position++;
1550 	if (this.position>=this.recipe.length) {
1551 		this.position = 0;
1552 	}
1553 	var item = this.recipe[this.position];
1554 	if (typeof(item)=='function') {
1555 		item();
1556 	} else if (item.element) {
1557 		hui.ani(item.element,item.property,item.value,item.duration,{ease:item.ease});
1558 	}
1559 	var self = this;
1560 	var time = item.duration || 0;
1561 	window.setTimeout(function() {self.next()},time);
1562 }
1563 
1564 hui.animation.Loop.prototype.start = function() {
1565 	this.running=true;
1566 	this.next();
1567 }
1568 
1569 /** @constructor */
1570 hui.Color = function(str) {
1571     this.ok = false;
1572 	if (hui.isBlank(str)) {
1573 		return;
1574 	}
1575     // strip any leading #
1576     if (str.charAt(0) == '#') { // remove # if any
1577         str = str.substr(1,6);
1578     }
1579 
1580     str = str.replace(/ /g,'');
1581     str = str.toLowerCase();
1582 		
1583     for (var key in hui.Color.table) {
1584         if (str == key) {
1585             str = hui.Color.table[key];
1586         }
1587     }
1588     // emd of simple type-in colors
1589 
1590     // array of color definition objects
1591     var color_defs = [
1592         {
1593             re: /^rgb\((\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3})\)$/,
1594             process: function (bits){
1595                 return [
1596                     parseInt(bits[1]),
1597                     parseInt(bits[2]),
1598                     parseInt(bits[3])
1599                 ];
1600             }
1601         },
1602         {
1603             re: /^rgb\((\d{1,3})%,\s*(\d{1,3})%,\s*(\d{1,3})%\)$/	,
1604             process: function (bits){
1605                 return [
1606                     Math.round(parseInt(bits[1])/100*255),
1607                     Math.round(parseInt(bits[2])/100*255),
1608                     Math.round(parseInt(bits[3])/100*255)
1609                 ];
1610             }
1611         },
1612         {
1613             re: /^(\w{2})(\w{2})(\w{2})$/,
1614             process: function (bits){
1615                 return [
1616                     parseInt(bits[1], 16),
1617                     parseInt(bits[2], 16),
1618                     parseInt(bits[3], 16)
1619                 ];
1620             }
1621         },
1622         {
1623             re: /^(\w{1})(\w{1})(\w{1})$/,
1624             process: function (bits){
1625                 return [
1626                     parseInt(bits[1] + bits[1], 16),
1627                     parseInt(bits[2] + bits[2], 16),
1628                     parseInt(bits[3] + bits[3], 16)
1629                 ];
1630             }
1631         }
1632     ];
1633 
1634     // search through the definitions to find a match
1635     for (var i = 0; i < color_defs.length; i++) {
1636         var re = color_defs[i].re,
1637 			processor = color_defs[i].process,
1638 			bits = re.exec(str);
1639         if (bits) {
1640             channels = processor(bits);
1641             this.r = channels[0];
1642             this.g = channels[1];
1643             this.b = channels[2];
1644             this.ok = true;
1645 			break;
1646         }
1647     }
1648 
1649     // validate/cleanup values
1650     this.r = (this.r < 0 || isNaN(this.r)) ? 0 : ((this.r > 255) ? 255 : this.r);
1651     this.g = (this.g < 0 || isNaN(this.g)) ? 0 : ((this.g > 255) ? 255 : this.g);
1652     this.b = (this.b < 0 || isNaN(this.b)) ? 0 : ((this.b > 255) ? 255 : this.b);
1653 }
1654 
1655 hui.Color.prototype = {
1656 	toRGB : function () {
1657         return 'rgb(' + this.r + ', ' + this.g + ', ' + this.b + ')';
1658     },
1659 	toHex : function() {
1660         var r = this.r.toString(16);
1661         var g = this.g.toString(16);
1662         var b = this.b.toString(16);
1663         if (r.length == 1) {
1664 			r = '0' + r;
1665 		}
1666         if (g.length == 1) {
1667 			g = '0' + g;
1668 		}
1669         if (b.length == 1) {
1670 			b = '0' + b;
1671 		}
1672         return '#' + r + g + b;
1673 	}
1674 }
1675 
1676 hui.Color.table = {
1677 	white : 'ffffff',
1678 	black : '000000',
1679 	red : 'ff0000',
1680 	green : '00ff00',
1681 	blue : '0000ff'
1682 }
1683 
1684 hui.Color.hex2rgb = function(hex) {
1685 	if (hui.isBlank(hex)) {
1686 		return null;
1687 	}
1688 	if (hex[0]=="#") {
1689 		hex=hex.substr(1);
1690 	}
1691 	if (hex.length==3) {
1692 		var temp=hex;
1693 		hex='';
1694 		temp = /^([a-f0-9])([a-f0-9])([a-f0-9])$/i.exec(temp).slice(1);
1695 		for (var i=0;i<3;i++) {
1696 			hex+=temp[i]+temp[i];
1697 		}
1698 	}
1699 	var triplets = /^([a-f0-9]{2})([a-f0-9]{2})([a-f0-9]{2})$/i.exec(hex).slice(1);
1700 	return {
1701 		r:   parseInt(triplets[0],16),
1702 		g: parseInt(triplets[1],16),
1703 		b:  parseInt(triplets[2],16)
1704 	}
1705 }
1706 
1707 hui.Color.hsv2rgb = function (Hdeg,S,V) {
1708   	var H = Hdeg/360,R,G,B;     // convert from degrees to 0 to 1
1709   	if (S==0) {       // HSV values = From 0 to 1
1710 		R = V*255;     // RGB results = From 0 to 255
1711 		G = V*255;
1712 		B = V*255;
1713 	} else {
1714     	var h = H*6,
1715 			var_r,var_g,var_b;
1716     	var i = Math.floor( h );
1717     	var var_1 = V*(1-S);
1718     	var var_2 = V*(1-S*(h-i));
1719     	var var_3 = V*(1-S*(1-(h-i)));
1720     	if (i==0) {
1721 			var_r=V ;
1722 			var_g=var_3;
1723 			var_b=var_1
1724 		}
1725     	else if (i==1) {
1726 			var_r=var_2;
1727 			var_g=V;
1728 			var_b=var_1
1729 		}
1730     	else if (i==2) {var_r=var_1; var_g=V;     var_b=var_3}
1731     	else if (i==3) {var_r=var_1; var_g=var_2; var_b=V}
1732     	else if (i==4) {var_r=var_3; var_g=var_1; var_b=V}
1733     	else {var_r=V;     var_g=var_1; var_b=var_2}
1734     	R = Math.round(var_r*255);   //RGB results = From 0 to 255
1735     	G = Math.round(var_g*255);
1736     	B = Math.round(var_b*255);
1737   	}
1738   	return new Array(R,G,B);
1739 }
1740 
1741 hui.Color.rgb2hsv = function(r, g, b) {
1742 
1743     r = (r / 255);
1744     g = (g / 255);
1745 	b = (b / 255);	
1746 
1747     var min = Math.min(Math.min(r, g), b),
1748         max = Math.max(Math.max(r, g), b),
1749 		value = max,
1750         saturation,
1751         hue;
1752 
1753     // Hue
1754     if (max == min) {
1755         hue = 0;
1756     } else if (max == r) {
1757         hue = (60 * ((g-b) / (max-min))) % 360;
1758     } else if (max == g) {
1759         hue = 60 * ((b-r) / (max-min)) + 120;
1760     } else if (max == b) {
1761         hue = 60 * ((r-g) / (max-min)) + 240;
1762     }
1763 
1764     if (hue < 0) {
1765         hue += 360;
1766     }
1767 
1768     // Saturation
1769     if (max == 0) {
1770         saturation = 0;
1771     } else {
1772         saturation = 1 - (min/max);
1773     }
1774 
1775     return [Math.round(hue), Math.round(saturation * 100), Math.round(value * 100)];
1776 }
1777 
1778 hui.Color.rgb2hex = function(rgbary) {
1779 	var c = '#';
1780   	for (var i=0; i < 3; i++) {
1781 		var str = parseInt(rgbary[i]).toString(16);
1782     	if (str.length < 2) {
1783 			str = '0'+str;
1784 		}
1785 		c+=str;
1786   	}
1787   	return c;
1788 }

1791 /** @namespace */
1792 hui.ease = {
1793 	slowFastSlow : function(val) {
1794 		var a = 1.6;
1795 		var b = 1.4;
1796 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
1797 	},
1798 	fastSlow : function(val) {
1799 		var a = .5;
1800 		var b = .7
1801 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
1802 	},
1803 	elastic : function(t) {
1804 		return 1 - hui.ease.elastic2(1-t);
1805 	},
1806 
1807 	elastic2 : function (t, a, p) {
1808 		if (t<=0 || t>=1) return t;
1809 		if (!p) p=0.45;
1810 		var s;
1811 		if (!a || a < 1) {
1812 			a=1;
1813 			s=p/4;
1814 		} else {
1815 			s = p/(2*Math.PI) * Math.asin (1/a);
1816 		}
1817 		return -(a*Math.pow(2,10*(t-=1)) * Math.sin( (t-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p ));
1818 	},
1819 	bounce : function(t) {
1820 		if (t < (1/2.75)) {
1821 			return 7.5625*t*t;
1822 		} else if (t < (2/2.75)) {
1823 			return (7.5625*(t-=(1.5/2.75))*t + .75);
1824 		} else if (t < (2.5/2.75)) {
1825 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.25/2.75))*t + .9375);
1826 		} else {
1827 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.625/2.75))*t + .984375);
1828 		}
1829 	},
1830 	flicker : function(value) {
1831 		if (value==1) return 1;
1832 		return Math.random()*value;
1833 	},
1834 	
1835 	linear: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1836 		// summary: A linear easing function
1837 		return n;
1838 	},
1839 
1840 	quadIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1841 		return Math.pow(n, 2);
1842 	},
1843 
1844 	quadOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1845 		return n * (n-2) * -1;
1846 	},
1847 
1848 	quadInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1849 		n=n*2;
1850 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 2) / 2; }
1851 		return -1 * ((--n)*(n-2) - 1) / 2;
1852 	},
1853 
1854 	cubicIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1855 		return Math.pow(n, 3);
1856 	},
1857 
1858 	cubicOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1859 		return Math.pow(n-1, 3) + 1;
1860 	},
1861 
1862 	cubicInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1863 		n=n*2;
1864 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 3) / 2; }
1865 		n-=2;
1866 		return (Math.pow(n, 3) + 2) / 2;
1867 	},
1868 
1869 	quartIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1870 		return Math.pow(n, 4);
1871 	},
1872 
1873 	quartOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1874 		return -1 * (Math.pow(n-1, 4) - 1);
1875 	},
1876 
1877 	quartInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1878 		n=n*2;
1879 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 4) / 2; }
1880 		n-=2;
1881 		return -1/2 * (Math.pow(n, 4) - 2);
1882 	},
1883 
1884 	quintIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1885 		return Math.pow(n, 5);
1886 	},
1887 
1888 	quintOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1889 		return Math.pow(n-1, 5) + 1;
1890 	},
1891 
1892 	quintInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1893 		n=n*2;
1894 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 5) / 2; };
1895 		n-=2;
1896 		return (Math.pow(n, 5) + 2) / 2;
1897 	},
1898 
1899 	sineIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1900 		return -1 * Math.cos(n * (Math.PI/2)) + 1;
1901 	},
1902 
1903 	sineOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1904 		return Math.sin(n * (Math.PI/2));
1905 	},
1906 
1907 	sineInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1908 		return -1 * (Math.cos(Math.PI*n) - 1) / 2;
1909 	},
1910 
1911 	expoIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1912 		return (n==0) ? 0 : Math.pow(2, 10 * (n - 1));
1913 	},
1914 
1915 	expoOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1916 		return (n==1) ? 1 : (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 1);
1917 	},
1918 
1919 	expoInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1920 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
1921 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
1922 		n = n*2;
1923 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(2, 10 * (n-1)) / 2; }
1924 		--n;
1925 		return (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 2) / 2;
1926 	},
1927 
1928 	circIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1929 		return -1 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1);
1930 	},
1931 
1932 	circOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1933 		n = n-1;
1934 		return Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2));
1935 	},
1936 
1937 	circInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1938 		n = n*2;
1939 		if(n<1){ return -1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1); }
1940 		n-=2;
1941 		return 1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) + 1);
1942 	},
1943 
1944 	backIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1945 		var s = 1.70158;
1946 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s+1)*n - s);
1947 	},
1948 
1949 	backOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1950 		// summary: an easing function that pops past the range briefly, and 
1951 		// 	slowly comes back. 
1952 		n = n - 1;
1953 		var s = 1.70158;
1954 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s + 1) * n + s) + 1;
1955 	},
1956 
1957 	backInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1958 		var s = 1.70158 * 1.525;
1959 		n = n*2;
1960 		if(n < 1){ return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n - s))/2; }
1961 		n-=2;
1962 		return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n + s) + 2)/2;
1963 	},
1964 
1965 	elasticIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1966 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
1967 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
1968 		var p = .3;
1969 		var s = p/4;
1970 		n = n - 1;
1971 		return -1 * Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p);
1972 	},
1973 
1974 	elasticOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1975 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the target value, near the end of the Animation
1976 		if(n==0) return 0;
1977 		if(n==1) return 1;
1978 		var p = .3;
1979 		var s = p/4;
1980 		return Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p) + 1;
1981 	},
1982 
1983 	elasticInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1984 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the value, near the beginning and end of the Animation		
1985 		if(n==0) return 0;
1986 		n = n*2;
1987 		if(n==2) return 1;
1988 		var p = .3*1.5;
1989 		var s = p/4;
1990 		if(n<1){
1991 			n-=1;
1992 			return -.5*(Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p));
1993 		}
1994 		n-=1;
1995 		return .5*(Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p)) + 1;
1996 	},
1997 
1998 	bounceIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1999 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the beginning of an Animation
2000 		return (1 - hui.ease.bounceOut(1-n)); // Decimal
2001 	},
2002 
2003 	bounceOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
2004 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the end of an Animation
2005 		var s=7.5625;
2006 		var p=2.75;
2007 		var l; 
2008 		if(n < (1 / p)){
2009 			l = s*Math.pow(n, 2);
2010 		}else if(n < (2 / p)){
2011 			n -= (1.5 / p);
2012 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .75;
2013 		}else if(n < (2.5 / p)){
2014 			n -= (2.25 / p);
2015 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .9375;
2016 		}else{
2017 			n -= (2.625 / p);
2018 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .984375;
2019 		}
2020 		return l;
2021 	},
2022 
2023 	bounceInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
2024 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" at the beginning and end of the Animation
2025 		if(n<0.5){ return hui.ease.bounceIn(n*2) / 2; }
2026 		return (hui.ease.bounceOut(n*2-1) / 2) + 0.5; // Decimal
2027 	}
2028 };

2031 	Function.prototype.bind = function () {
2032 	    if (arguments.length < 2 && arguments[0] === undefined) {
2033 	        return this;
2034 	    }
2035 	    var thisObj = this,
2036 	    args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments),
2037 	    obj = args.shift();
2038 	    return function () {
2039 	        return thisObj.apply(obj, args.concat(Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments)));
2040 	    };
2041 	};
2042 
2043 	Function.bind = function() {
2044 	    var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
2045 	    return Function.prototype.bind.apply(args.shift(), args);
2046 	}
2047 }

2052 			.replace(/\/\/.*?[\r\n]|\/\*(?:.|[\r\n])*?\*\//g, '')
2053 			.replace(/\s+/g, '').split(',');
2054 		return names.length == 1 && !names[0] ? [] : names;

2091   var $script = function(paths, idOrDone, optDone) {
2092     paths = paths[push] ? paths : [paths];
2093     var idOrDoneIsDone = idOrDone && idOrDone.call,
2094         done = idOrDoneIsDone ? idOrDone : optDone,
2095         id = idOrDoneIsDone ? paths.join('') : idOrDone,
2096         queue = paths.length;
2097         function loopFn(item) {
2098           return item.call ? item() : list[item];
2099         }
2100         function callback() {
2101           if (!--queue) {
2102             list[id] = 1;
2103             done && done();
2104             for (var dset in delay) {
2105               every(dset.split('|'), loopFn) && !each(delay[dset], loopFn) && (delay[dset] = []);
2106             }
2107           }
2108         }
2109     timeout(function() {
2110       each(paths, function(path) {
2111         if (scripts[path]) {
2112           id && (ids[id] = 1);
2113           callback();
2114           return;
2115         }
2116         scripts[path] = 1;
2117         id && (ids[id] = 1);
2118         create($script.path ?
2119           $script.path + path + '.js' :
2120           path, callback);
2121       });
2122     }, 0);

2127     var el = doc.createElement("script"),
2128         loaded = f;
2129     el.onload = el.onerror = el[onreadystatechange] = function () {
2130       if ((el[readyState] && !(/^c|loade/.test(el[readyState]))) || loaded) {
2131         return;
2132       }
2133       el.onload = el[onreadystatechange] = null;
2134       loaded = 1;
2135       fn();
2136     };
2137     el.async = 1;

2148       list[dep] || missing[push](dep);
2149     }) && every(deps, function(dep) {
2150       return list[dep];
2151     }) ? ready() : !function(key) {
2152       delay[key] = delay[key] || [];
2153       delay[key][push](ready);

2257 		this.settings[settingName] = (this.settings[settingName] == undefined) ? defaultValue : this.settings[settingName];

2260 	// Upload backend settings

2323 SWFUpload.prototype.loadFlash = function () {
2324 	if (this.settings.button_placeholder_id !== "") {
2325 		this.replaceWithFlash();
2326 	} else {
2327 		this.appendFlash();
2328 	}

2331 // Private: appendFlash gets the HTML tag for the Flash
2332 // It then appends the flash to the body
2333 SWFUpload.prototype.appendFlash = function () {
2334 	var targetElement, container;
2335 
2336 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
2337 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
2338 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
2339 	}
2340 
2341 	// Get the body tag where we will be adding the flash movie
2342 	targetElement = document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0];
2343 
2344 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
2345 		throw "Could not find the 'body' element.";
2346 	}
2347 
2348 	// Append the container and load the flash
2349 	container = document.createElement("div");
2350 	container.style.width = "1px";
2351 	container.style.height = "1px";
2352 	container.style.overflow = "hidden";
2353 
2354 	targetElement.appendChild(container);
2355 	container.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
2356 };
2357 
2358 // Private: replaceWithFlash replaces the button_placeholder element with the flash movie.
2359 SWFUpload.prototype.replaceWithFlash = function () {
2360 	var targetElement, tempParent;
2361 
2362 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
2363 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
2364 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
2365 	}
2366 	// Get the element where we will be placing the flash movie
2367 	targetElement = this.settings.button_placeholder || document.getElementById(this.settings.button_placeholder_id);
2368 
2369 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
2370 		throw "Could not find the placeholder element.";
2371 	}
2372 
2373 	// Append the container and load the flash
2374 	tempParent = document.createElement("div");
2375 	tempParent.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
2376 	targetElement.parentNode.replaceChild(tempParent.firstChild, targetElement);
2377 };

2379 // Private: getFlashHTML generates the object tag needed to embed the flash in to the document
2380 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashHTML = function () {
2381 	var transparent = this.settings.button_image_url === "" ? true : false;
2382 	
2383 	// Flash Satay object syntax: http://www.alistapart.com/articles/flashsatay
2384 	return ['<object id="', this.movieName, '" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="', this.settings.flash_url, '" width="', this.settings.button_width, '" height="', this.settings.button_height, '" class="swfupload">',
2385 				'<param name="wmode" value="', transparent ? "transparent" : "window", '" />',
2386 				'<param name="movie" value="', this.settings.flash_url, '" />',
2387 				'<param name="quality" value="high" />',
2388 				'<param name="menu" value="false" />',
2389 				'<param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" />',
2390 				'<param name="flashvars" value="' + this.getFlashVars() + '" />',
2391 				'</object>'].join("");
2392 };

2394 // Private: getFlashVars builds the parameter string that will be passed
2395 // to flash in the flashvars param.
2396 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashVars = function () {
2397 	// Build a string from the post param object
2398 	var paramString = this.buildParamString();
2399 
2400 	// Build the parameter string
2401 	return ["movieName=", encodeURIComponent(this.movieName),
2402 			"&uploadURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.upload_url),
2403 			"&useQueryString=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.use_query_string),
2404 			"&requeueOnError=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.requeue_on_error),
2405 			"&params=", encodeURIComponent(paramString),
2406 			"&filePostName=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_post_name),
2407 			"&fileTypes=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types),
2408 			"&fileTypesDescription=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types_description),
2409 			"&fileSizeLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_size_limit),
2410 			"&fileUploadLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_upload_limit),
2411 			"&fileQueueLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_queue_limit),
2412 			"&debugEnabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.debug_enabled),
2413 			"&buttonImageURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_image_url),
2414 			"&buttonWidth=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_width),
2415 			"&buttonHeight=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_height),
2416 			"&buttonText=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text),
2417 			"&buttonTextTopPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_top_padding),
2418 			"&buttonTextLeftPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_left_padding),
2419 			"&buttonTextStyle=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_style),
2420 			"&buttonAction=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_action),
2421 			"&buttonDisabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_disabled)
2422 		].join("");

2425 // Public: getMovieElement retrieves the DOM reference to the Flash element added by SWFUpload
2426 // The element is cached after the first lookup
2427 SWFUpload.prototype.getMovieElement = function () {
2428 	if (this.movieElement == undefined) {
2429 		this.movieElement = document.getElementById(this.movieName);
2430 	}
2431 
2432 	if (this.movieElement === null) {
2433 		throw "Could not find Flash element";
2434 	}
2435 	
2436 	return this.movieElement;

2439 // Private: buildParamString takes the name/value pairs in the post_params setting object
2440 // and joins them up in to a string formatted "name=value&name=value"
2441 SWFUpload.prototype.buildParamString = function () {
2442 	var postParams = this.settings.post_params; 
2443 	var paramStringPairs = [];
2444 
2445 	if (typeof(postParams) === "object") {
2446 		for (var name in postParams) {
2447 			if (postParams.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
2448 				paramStringPairs.push(encodeURIComponent(name.toString()) + "=" + encodeURIComponent(postParams[name].toString()));
2449 			}
2450 		}
2451 	}
2452 
2453 	return paramStringPairs.join("&");
2454 };

2456 // Public: Used to remove a SWFUpload instance from the page. This method strives to remove
2457 // all references to the SWF, and other objects so memory is properly freed.
2458 // Returns true if everything was destroyed. Returns a false if a failure occurs leaving SWFUpload in an inconsistant state.
2459 SWFUpload.prototype.destroy = function () {
2460 	try {
2461 		// Make sure Flash is done before we try to remove it
2462 		this.stopUpload();
2463 		
2464 		// Remove the SWFUpload DOM nodes
2465 		var movieElement = null;
2466 		try {
2467 			movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2468 		} catch (ex) {
2469 		}
2470 		
2471 		if (movieElement != undefined && movieElement.parentNode != undefined && typeof movieElement.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
2472 			var container = movieElement.parentNode;
2473 			if (container != undefined) {
2474 				container.removeChild(movieElement);
2475 				if (container.parentNode != undefined && typeof container.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
2476 					container.parentNode.removeChild(container);
2477 				}
2478 			}
2479 		}
2480 		
2481 		// Destroy references
2482 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = null;
2483 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
2484 
2485 		delete this.movieElement;
2486 		delete this.settings;
2487 		delete this.customSettings;
2488 		delete this.eventQueue;
2489 		delete this.movieName;
2490 		
2491 		delete window[this.movieName];
2492 		
2493 		return true;
2494 	} catch (ex1) {
2495 		return false;
2496 	}
2497 };

2574 // Private: callFlash handles function calls made to the Flash element.
2575 // Calls are made with a setTimeout for some functions to work around
2576 // bugs in the ExternalInterface library.
2577 SWFUpload.prototype.callFlash = function (functionName, argumentArray) {
2578 	argumentArray = argumentArray || [];
2579 	
2580 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2581 	var returnValue;
2582 
2583 	if (typeof movieElement[functionName] === "function") {
2584 		// We have to go through all this if/else stuff because the Flash functions don't have apply() and only accept the exact number of arguments.
2585 		if (argumentArray.length === 0) {
2586 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName]();
2587 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 1) {
2588 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0]);
2589 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 2) {
2590 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1]);
2591 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 3) {
2592 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1], argumentArray[2]);
2593 		} else {
2594 			throw "Too many arguments";
2595 		}
2596 		
2597 		// Unescape file post param values
2598 		if (returnValue != undefined && typeof returnValue.post === "object") {
2599 			returnValue = this.unescapeFilePostParams(returnValue);
2600 		}
2601 		
2602 		return returnValue;
2603 	} else {
2604 		throw "Invalid function name: " + functionName;
2605 	}
2606 };

2818 /* *******************************
2819 	Flash Event Interfaces
2820 	These functions are used by Flash to trigger the various
2821 	events.
2822 	
2823 	All these functions a Private.
2824 	
2825 	Because the ExternalInterface library is buggy the event calls
2826 	are added to a queue and the queue then executed by a setTimeout.
2827 	This ensures that events are executed in a determinate order and that
2828 	the ExternalInterface bugs are avoided.
2829 ******************************* */
2830 
2831 SWFUpload.prototype.queueEvent = function (handlerName, argumentArray) {
2832 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
2833 	
2834 	if (argumentArray == undefined) {
2835 		argumentArray = [];
2836 	} else if (!(argumentArray instanceof Array)) {
2837 		argumentArray = [argumentArray];
2838 	}
2839 	
2840 	var self = this;
2841 	if (typeof this.settings[handlerName] === "function") {
2842 		// Queue the event
2843 		this.eventQueue.push(function () {
2844 			this.settings[handlerName].apply(this, argumentArray);
2845 		});
2846 		
2847 		// Execute the next queued event
2848 		setTimeout(function () {
2849 			self.executeNextEvent();
2850 		}, 0);
2851 		
2852 	} else if (this.settings[handlerName] !== null) {
2853 		throw "Event handler " + handlerName + " is unknown or is not a function";
2854 	}
2855 };
2856 
2857 // Private: Causes the next event in the queue to be executed.  Since events are queued using a setTimeout
2858 // we must queue them in order to garentee that they are executed in order.
2859 SWFUpload.prototype.executeNextEvent = function () {
2860 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
2861 
2862 	var  f = this.eventQueue ? this.eventQueue.shift() : null;
2863 	if (typeof(f) === "function") {
2864 		f.apply(this);
2865 	}
2866 };
2867 
2868 // Private: unescapeFileParams is part of a workaround for a flash bug where objects passed through ExternalInterface cannot have
2869 // properties that contain characters that are not valid for JavaScript identifiers. To work around this
2870 // the Flash Component escapes the parameter names and we must unescape again before passing them along.
2871 SWFUpload.prototype.unescapeFilePostParams = function (file) {
2872 	var reg = /[$]([0-9a-f]{4})/i;
2873 	var unescapedPost = {};
2874 	var uk;
2875 
2876 	if (file != undefined) {
2877 		for (var k in file.post) {
2878 			if (file.post.hasOwnProperty(k)) {
2879 				uk = k;
2880 				var match;
2881 				while ((match = reg.exec(uk)) !== null) {
2882 					uk = uk.replace(match[0], String.fromCharCode(parseInt("0x" + match[1], 16)));
2883 				}
2884 				unescapedPost[uk] = file.post[k];
2885 			}
2886 		}
2887 
2888 		file.post = unescapedPost;
2889 	}
2890 
2891 	return file;
2892 };
2893 
2894 SWFUpload.prototype.flashReady = function () {
2895 	// Check that the movie element is loaded correctly with its ExternalInterface methods defined
2896 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2897 	if (typeof movieElement.StartUpload !== "function") {
2898 		throw "ExternalInterface methods failed to initialize.";
2899 	}
2900 
2901 	// Fix IE Flash/Form bug
2902 	if (window[this.movieName] == undefined) {
2903 		window[this.movieName] = movieElement;
2904 	}
2905 	
2906 	this.queueEvent("swfupload_loaded_handler");
2907 };

2940 SWFUpload.prototype.returnUploadStart = function (file) {
2941 	var returnValue;
2942 	if (typeof this.settings.upload_start_handler === "function") {
2943 		file = this.unescapeFilePostParams(file);
2944 		returnValue = this.settings.upload_start_handler.call(this, file);
2945 	} else if (this.settings.upload_start_handler != undefined) {
2946 		throw "upload_start_handler must be a function";
2947 	}
2948 
2949 	// Convert undefined to true so if nothing is returned from the upload_start_handler it is
2950 	// interpretted as 'true'.
2951 	if (returnValue === undefined) {
2952 		returnValue = true;
2953 	}
2954 	
2955 	returnValue = !!returnValue;
2956 	
2957 	this.callFlash("ReturnUploadStart", [returnValue]);
2958 };

2983    internal debug console.  You can override this event and have messages written where you want. */

2987 /*
2988     json2.js
2989     2008-01-17
2990 
2991     Public Domain
2992 
2993     No warranty expressed or implied. Use at your own risk.
2994 
2995     See http://www.JSON.org/js.html
2996 
2997     This file creates a global JSON object containing two methods:
2998 
2999         JSON.stringify(value, whitelist)
3000             value       any JavaScript value, usually an object or array.
3001 
3002             whitelist   an optional array prameter that determines how object
3003                         values are stringified.
3004 
3005             This method produces a JSON text from a JavaScript value.
3006             There are three possible ways to stringify an object, depending
3007             on the optional whitelist parameter.
3008 
3009             If an object has a toJSON method, then the toJSON() method will be
3010             called. The value returned from the toJSON method will be
3011             stringified.
3012 
3013             Otherwise, if the optional whitelist parameter is an array, then
3014             the elements of the array will be used to select members of the
3015             object for stringification.
3016 
3017             Otherwise, if there is no whitelist parameter, then all of the
3018             members of the object will be stringified.
3019 
3020             Values that do not have JSON representaions, such as undefined or
3021             functions, will not be serialized. Such values in objects will be
3022             dropped; in arrays will be replaced with null.
3023             JSON.stringify(undefined) returns undefined. Dates will be
3024             stringified as quoted ISO dates.
3025 
3026             Example:
3027 
3028             var text = JSON.stringify(['e', {pluribus: 'unum'}]);
3029             // text is '["e",{"pluribus":"unum"}]'
3030 
3031         JSON.parse(text, filter)
3032             This method parses a JSON text to produce an object or
3033             array. It can throw a SyntaxError exception.
3034 
3035             The optional filter parameter is a function that can filter and
3036             transform the results. It receives each of the keys and values, and
3037             its return value is used instead of the original value. If it
3038             returns what it received, then structure is not modified. If it
3039             returns undefined then the member is deleted.
3040 
3041             Example:
3042 
3043             // Parse the text. If a key contains the string 'date' then
3044             // convert the value to a date.
3045 
3046             myData = JSON.parse(text, function (key, value) {
3047                 return key.indexOf('date') >= 0 ? new Date(value) : value;
3048             });
3049 
3050     This is a reference implementation. You are free to copy, modify, or
3051     redistribute.
3052 
3053     Use your own copy. It is extremely unwise to load third party
3054     code into your pages.
3055 */
3056
